These '''[[Shrunken head|Shrunken Heads]] '''hung in the entrance of the [[Three Broomsticks Inn]].<ref name="POAF">{{POA|F}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
{{Dialogue a-b-c|Shrunken Head|I say! No underage wizards allowed in today! Shut the damn door!|Hermione|So rude.|Ron|Thick heads.|Hermione and Ron to the talking Shrunken Heads guarding [[Three Broomsticks Inn]] in [[1993]]|Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film)}}
*In the film version, during a [[Hogsmeade]] weekend visit in the [[1993–1994 school year]], they stopped [[Ronald Weasley|Ron Weasley]] and [[Hermione Granger]] from entering the pub, as no underage [[Wizardkind|wizards]] were allowed in that day. [[Harry Potter]], however, was able to slip past them under his [[Cloak of Invisibility|Invisibility Cloak]].
*The shrunken heads were voiced by Brian Bowles and Peter Serafinowicz in the film adaptation of {{POA}}.{{Fact}} Bowles also played the [[Headless Horseman]] in the same film.{{Fact}}
*In the DS version of {{LEGO|Y1}}, they are replaced by a wizard guarding the [[Three Broomsticks Inn]].
*The middle shrunken head bears a slight resemblance to [[Dre Head]].

