'''Caretaker''' was the title and occupation held at [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry]] by a [[Wizardkind|witch]], [[Wizardkind|wizard]], or [[Squib]] in charge of overseeing the cleanliness and hygiene of [[Hogwarts Castle]]. Aside from this, they could patrol the corridors at night to make sure that no students wandered in the late hours.<ref name="PS8">{{PS|B|8}}</ref><ref name="PS9">{{PS|B|9}}</ref><ref name="PS12">{{PS|B|12}}</ref> In the past, they were also in charge of corporal punishment (e.g. caning)<ref name="GOF31">{{GOF|B|31}}</ref> until [[Headmaster]] [[Albus Dumbledore]] banned it. However, the job did still entail helping to oversee punishments, as in [[1992]], when [[Ronald Weasley]]'s [[Discipline at Hogwarts#Detention|detention]] was to help [[Argus Filch]] polish the school's trophies without using any [[magic]].<ref name="COS7">{{COS|B|7}}</ref>

The Caretaker of Hogwarts also possessed some disciplinary powers, being able to award and dock house points. In [[1987]], [[Argus Filch]] reluctantly awarded [[Jacob's sibling]] ten house points at the behest of the [[Gryffindor]] house ghost, [[Sir Nicholas de Mimsy-Porpington]].<ref name="HM">{{HM}} {{c|Player-determined.}}</ref>

==Duties==
Some duties of the caretaker included:
*Enforcing hygiene of the school and the students.
*Patrolling corridors for students out of bed after hours or in forbidden areas.<ref name="PS9"/>
*Handing out corporal punishment (formerly).<ref name="COS8">{{COS|B|8}}</ref><ref name="GOF31"/>
*Putting students in [[Discipline at Hogwarts#Detention|detention]].<ref name="PS15">{{PS|B|15}}</ref><ref name="COS7"/>
*Doing jobs that the [[Headmaster]] required.
*Investigating things such as [[Dungbomb]]s or mayhem.<ref name="POA10">{{POA|B|10}}</ref><ref name="OOTP14">{{OOTP|B|14}}</ref><ref name="OOTP29"/>
*Being in charge of security for [[Hogsmeade]] trips,<ref name="POA8">{{POA|B|8}}</ref> mail,<ref name="OOTP14"/> and people entering and leaving the castle.<ref name="HBP8">{{HBP|B|8}}</ref>

==Known Caretakers==
===Hankerton Humble===
[[Hankerton Humble]] was the first ever caretaker of Hogwarts, appointed directly by the school founders. He often clashed with [[Peeves]].<ref name="pottermorepeeves">{{WW|peeves}}</ref>

===Rancorous Carpe===
[[Rancorous Carpe]] was a caretaker who was active at Hogwarts in [[1876]]. He was responsible for a disastrous attempt to remove Peeves, the resident [[Poltergeist]], in which he devised an elaborate trap baited with an assortment of weapons he believed would be irresistible to Peeves and a vast enchanted bell jar reinforced by various [[Containment Charm]]s, which he intended to drop over the poltergeist once he was in place. The trap failed spectacularly, with Peeves confiscating the weapons, resulting in a three-day standoff. Carpe took early retirement for health reasons.<ref name="pottermorepeeves" />

===Apollyon Pringle===
{{Quote|[[Arthur Weasley|Your father]] and [[Molly Weasley|I]] had been for a night-time stroll. He got caught by [[Apollyon Pringle]] - he was the caretaker in those days - your father's still got the marks.|[[Molly Weasley]] to her son, [[William Weasley|Bill]].|Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire}}[[Apollyon Pringle]] was the caretaker at [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry|Hogwarts]] from at least [[1961]] to [[1968]]. During his tenure, corporal punishment was allowed, and Mr Pringle was entitled to cane any student found wandering the corridors at night. At one time, at about four o'clock in the morning, he caught [[Arthur Weasley]] strolling about the [[Hogwarts Castle|castle]] and caned him while [[Molly Weasley|Molly Prewett]], who had been with Arthur, escaped. It was said by Molly, in the [[1994–1995 school year]], that Arthur still had the marks inflicted on him.<ref name="GOF31"/> By [[1973]], Mr Pringle had retired, died, or left the school, and was replaced by [[Argus Filch]] and his cat, [[Mrs Norris]].

===Argus Filch===
[[File:Filch & mrs. norris-1-.jpg|200px|thumb|right|[[Argus Filch]] and [[Mrs Norris]]]] 
By at least [[1973]], [[Argus Filch]], a [[Squib]], had replaced Pringle as Caretaker of [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry|Hogwarts School]]. He, along with his cat, [[Mrs Norris]], frequently patrolled the corridors at night and delighted in punishing students; he desired torturous methods for punishments, such as those inflicted by Pringle, but Dumbledore did not grant him such rights. He also waged an endless war with the school's [[poltergeist]], Peeves. He constantly hassled students over the littlest infraction and took delight in the doling out of detention-worthy write-ups.<ref name="PS8"/> In [[1995]], when [[Dolores Umbridge]] was made [[Headmaster|Headmistress]], Filch was allowed to use corporal punishment on students,<ref name="OOTP29">{{OOTP|B|29}}</ref> though it was revoked at the end of the year. He also continued as caretaker through [[Severus Snape]]'s tenure as [[Headmaster]], and it is unknown how Filch was treated under the tyranny of the [[Alecto and Amycus Carrow|Carrows]], given how he was a Squib. It is likely that Filch remained at the school after their removal.

